From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Date: Sun, 18 Jan 2026 06:15:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 6/9] fix: Normalize graph test for cross-platform hash
 differences

std::hash<std::string> produces different values on libstdc++ vs libc++,
causing the avalanche scheduler graph test to fail on macOS. Normalize
obj_* IDs by their labels and sort lines for platform-independent comparison.
---
 .../avalanche_scheduler/test_simple_test.py   | 63 ++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 49 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/GaudiHive/tests/pytest/avalanche_scheduler/test_simple_test.py b/GaudiHive/tests/pytest/avalanche_scheduler/test_simple_test.py
